metadata.name: The Great Annihilator #96
metadata.description:
One day you wake up,
All words are meaningless
And you can feel the light inside your mouth
Where everything were assembled and annihilated
Swallow the air, swallow all particle
A taste of burnt metal and ethyl
One thousand years of living souls
And you, are no more



=========

Controls:

[1] Set resolution to 716 x 1024px (default)

[2] Set resolution to 1433 x 2048px

[3] Set resolution to 2688 x 3840px

* The presets above are suitable for screen viewing up to 4k screen resolution. To set a custom resolution for printing and other purpose, add &res=[desired resolution] at the end of the URL. It will set the height of the image, and the width will be calculated automatically at 0.7 ratio. For example to get a resolution of 4911 x 7016px (about the size of A2 paper), add &res=7016 as URL parameter.

[c] Capture a screenshot at rendered resolution


Notes:

* This project use shaders that relies on GPU. Hi-res output may slow down your device. Since it also utilize GPU instance for thumbnail rendering, expect longer time for every iterations to be signed by fx(hash).

* If 'glitching' occurs or the composition behaves differently at different resolution, just refresh the page to reset it.

Made with cables.gl, a node-based webgl environment

XALTED 2023

As Bruno Munari said:

“Complicare è facile, semplificare é difficile. Per complicare basta aggiungere, tutto quello che si vuole: colori, forme, azioni, decorazioni, personaggi, ambienti pieni di cose. Tutti sono capaci di complicare. Pochi sono capaci di semplificare."

metadata.name: Bayeux #89
metadata.description:
Each output is generated by layering Blender renders.

'Bayeux' explores the bold simplicity and beauty of Bauhaus design ideas, with an arrangment of simple bauhaus-inspired shapes in a colorful, striking design. The addition of smaller shapes arranged in a checkerboard style gives some outputs an heraldic feel.

To download a 1500x2000px PNG:
Click/tap 'open', then click/tap the image to make a "Download image" button appear.

metadata.name: Linetract #122
metadata.description:
Art unites people, the same is also true with Artists.

"Linetract" is a collaborative work of two different artist: @Jolie__Michel and @Uniray_net 
Different backgrounds, different styles, same passion for creativity and Art!

"Linetract" is an abstract composition of simple shapes forms and colors, merged into a final minimal and hopefully aesthetic interesting result :)

CONTROLS

KEYS:

- 1-4: Set resolution from 1x to 4x of the current dimension (possibly slower performance in higher values)
- S: Save a png file with the current resolution

Made with p5js and custom shaders

Collaboration project by @Jolie__Michel and @Uniray_net
© January 2023

metadata.name: All The Way #102
metadata.description:
"All the Way" is a visually stunning and dynamic generative art piece that is sure to make a striking addition to any art collection. Created using the programming language p5js, this artwork is truly one of a kind and cannot be replicated.

The vibrant colors, fluid shapes, and dynamic movement in "All the Way" make it an ideal centerpiece for any space. The constantly shifting shapes and colors create a sense of energy and motion that will draw the eye and captivate the viewer. This piece is perfect for anyone who loves abstract art or is looking for something unique and eye-catching to add to their collection.

Additionally, the theme of "All the Way" is one that is sure to resonate with many people. The artwork represents the flow of life, the power of creativity, and the endless possibilities that exist in the world around us. This makes it an ideal choice for anyone who values personal growth, exploration, and a sense of adventure.

Whether you're an art collector, an art enthusiast, or simply someone who appreciates beautiful and thought-provoking art, "All the Way" is a must-have addition to your collection. With its dynamic and abstract style, this piece is sure to spark conversations and inspire new ideas. Don't miss out on the chance to own a truly unique and captivating artwork that you will enjoy for years to come!

To save image press "s"
To save image in high quality add &print=2 or &print=3 in the live URL then press "s".

Note: Image can take a minute to render.

Created using p5js and p5js pattern
Created By Winston
Feb 2023

metadata.name: The Distant peaks #21
metadata.description:
The Distant Peaks is the first generative art release that combines my collection on Objkt:
"The Windless Summit and The Distant sea"

Since the beginning, I want to create a plotter printer or generative art style. but I don't have the basic knowledge to do creative coding, so I tried to replicate it with The Help of artificial intelligence and now I'm collaborating with @rosetta196 to help me experiment with the generative art area.

Each piece in this collection is a unique and intricate representation of the rugged peaks and sweeping vistas of mountains, as well as the calming of the ocean's waves. The colors, textures, and movements of the artwork are all meticulously crafted through code, with every detail carefully considered to capture the essence of these natural wonders.

The use of pure code to generate these landscapes serves to highlight the beauty and complexity of mathematics and computer programming. 
It is a testament to the power of technology and its ability to create stunning works of art that evoke deep emotions and inspire creativity.

As you gaze upon the art, you are drawn into a world of tranquility and natural beauty. The peacefulness of the mountains and the endless expanse of the ocean come to life, inviting you to explore and discover the wonders of the natural world. 
This art project is a celebration of the beauty of nature and the incredible potential of generative art.


by Samanta and Rosetta196 2023

metadata.name: RotatingUnit #46
metadata.description:
《旋转单位》

既然还没认清生活的真相，这次就别选什么英雄主义了。
Since you haven't seen the world as it is, maybe it's best to skip the heroism this time around.





p5.js


Interact with the canvas via your mouse.
------------
Press 'i' -> info.
(📱Press and hold for 1s -> info.)
------------
Press 's' (fullscreen) -> png.
Add "&px=" to the end of the url to change the resolution in the range (1-6), the default is 2.
(For example: &px=4, you will get an image with 4 times the size of the window.)
